# Finance Data Processing & Access Control Backend

## 🚀 Overview

This project is a backend system for a finance dashboard where users interact with financial records based on their roles.

The system demonstrates:

* Role-based access control (RBAC)
* Financial records management
* Dashboard analytics (aggregations)
* Clean backend architecture using services, controllers, and middleware

---

## 🧱 Tech Stack

* Node.js
* Express.js
* PostgreSQL
* Prisma ORM
* JWT Authentication
* Zod (Validation)

---

## ⚙️ Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone Repository

```
git clone <your-repo-link>
cd finance-backend
```

### 2. Install Dependencies

```
npm install
```

### 3. Setup Environment Variables

Create `.env` file:

```
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://username:password@localhost:5432/finance_db
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key
PORT=5000
```

### 4. Run Database Migration

```
npx prisma migrate dev
```

### 5. Seed Initial Data (optional but recommended)

```
node seed.js
```

### 6. Start Server

```
npm run dev
```

---

## 🔐 Authentication APIs

### Register

```
POST /api/auth/register
```

### Login

```
POST /api/auth/login
```

---

## 👤 User Management (ADMIN only)

### Get All Users

```
GET /api/users
```

### Update User Role

```
PATCH /api/users/:id/role
```

### Update User Status

```
PATCH /api/users/:id/status
```

---

## 💰 Financial Records APIs

### Create Record (ADMIN)

```
POST /api/records
```

### Get Records (ADMIN, ANALYST)

```
GET /api/records
```

### Update Record (ADMIN)

```
PATCH /api/records/:id
```

### Delete Record (ADMIN)

```
DELETE /api/records/:id
```

### Filtering Examples

```
GET /api/records?type=EXPENSE
GET /api/records?category=Food
GET /api/records?from=2026-04-01&to=2026-04-30
```

---

## 📊 Dashboard APIs

### Summary

```
GET /api/dashboard/summary
```

Returns:

* Total Income
* Total Expenses
* Net Balance

---

### Category Breakdown

```
GET /api/dashboard/category
```

---

### Recent Activity

```
GET /api/dashboard/recent
```

---

### Trends

```
GET /api/dashboard/trends
```

---

## 🔑 Role-Based Access Control

| Role    | Permissions                               |
| ------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| Viewer  | Can access dashboard only                 |
| Analyst | Can view records + dashboard              |
| Admin   | Full access (users + records + dashboard) |

---

## ✅ Features Implemented

* User authentication using JWT
* Role-based access control (RBAC)
* Financial records CRUD operations
* Filtering (date, category, type)
* Dashboard analytics (aggregations)
* Input validation using Zod
* Centralized error handling
* Clean architecture (controller → service → DB)

---

## ⚠️ Assumptions & Decisions

* PostgreSQL used for structured financial data
* JWT used for stateless authentication
* Date is normalized in backend for consistency
* Role enforcement handled via middleware
* Trends grouped by date (can be extended to monthly)

---

## 🧪 Testing

All endpoints were tested using Postman:

* Role-based access verified
* Edge cases handled (invalid input, unauthorized access)
* Dashboard values verified manually

---

## 🚀 Future Improvements

* Pagination for records
* Monthly trend aggregation
* Soft delete functionality
* Swagger API documentation
* Unit tests

---

## 📌 Conclusion

This project demonstrates a clean and scalable backend system with proper separation of concerns, access control, and data processing logic. It reflects practical backend engineering principles required for real-world applications.

